- title 'About'
= render layout: 'layouts/partials/topper_stopper', locals: {row_top_title: 'About Crossword Café'} do
  .xw-prose
    %h2 What
    %p
      Crossword Café is a place for crossword enthusiasts to create, solve and share puzzles for free. No subscriptions or hassle.
    %h2 Why
    %p
      This site exists because I
      %del was
      am poor and
      %del didn't
      don't have a printer.
    %p
      My friend emailed me a crossword that he'd written, and I couldn't print it to solve it. So I built the first iteration of Crossword Café, a simple Javascript site to recreate his puzzle.
    %p
      I began looking for sites and applications that would help me write my own crossword puzzles and couldn't find anything. Well, nothing that wasn't expensive, ugly and/or missing features.
    %p
      So I kept working on Crossword Café.

    %h2 Who
    %p
      \...it's just me. My name's Dylan — I'm a developer who enjoys crosswords more than I'm good at them. My goal is for Will Shortz to one day disdainfully say "Crossword Café? Doesn't ring a bell."

    %h2 The Resurrection
    %p
      I built Crossword Café in 2013 and worked on it through 2014. Then life happened. The framework got old, the dependencies broke, and by 2018 it was basically a dead Rails 5 app that I couldn't bring myself to delete but also couldn't find the energy to fix.
    %p
      It sat like that for eight years. I'd open the repo every now and then, see the wall of deprecation warnings, and close my laptop.
    %p
      In February 2026, I used an AI coding tool to help me bring it back. Over a few days, the app went from Rails 5 to Rails 8, Ruby 2 to 3.4, got a real test suite, a new front end, and a working deploy. Honestly, it was months of work that I was never going to do on my own.
    %p
      I should be upfront about that — an AI wrote a lot of the code you're looking at. I made the decisions, reviewed everything, and built the original thing from scratch, but I had a lot of help with the heavy lifting. It's a weird thing to admit as a developer. But the other option was a dead site that nobody could use, so here we are.
    %p
      Still figuring out how I feel about it. But the café is open again, and that part feels good.

    = link_to 'Browse Puzzles', root_path, class: 'xw-btn'
